# ============================================================================
# YOUTUBE OAUTH (Required for YouTube Channel Linking)
# ============================================================================
# 
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: YouTube uses the SAME Google Cloud OAuth credentials as
# Google Sign-In (GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID / GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET). Both flows
# share the same OAuth 2.0 Client in Google Cloud Console — the difference
# is only the redirect URI and OAuth scopes.
# 
# So in .env.local, YOUTUBE_CLIENT_ID = same value as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
#                  YOUTUBE_CLIENT_SECRET = same value as GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET
#
# How to set up for development:
# 
# 1. Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing
# 3. Enable "YouTube Data API v3":
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Library"
#    - Search for "YouTube Data API v3"
#    - Click "Enable"
# 4. Edit your EXISTING OAuth 2.0 Client ID (same one used for Google Sign-In):
#    - Add these redirect URIs (don't create a new client):
#      * http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/youtube
#      * http://localhost:3000/api/youtube/link/callback
#    - Click "Save"
# 5. You DON'T need new credentials — copy the same GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID/SECRET below
# 6. Fill in the values below (same values as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID / GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET)
# 
# Note: YOUTUBE_CLIENT_ID is server-only (never exposed to browser)
#       YOUTUBE_CLIENT_SECRET is sensitive - keep it secret!
# 
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
# (SAME value as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID)
YOUTUBE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id-here
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
# (SAME value as GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET)
YOUTUBE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret-here
# YouTube OAuth Redirect URI (development — used by generic OAuth flow at /api/oauth/callback/youtube)
# The frontend calls /api/oauth/authorize/youtube, which redirects here.
# Must match what's registered in Google Cloud Console > OAuth 2.0 Client > Authorized redirect URIs
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
YOUTUBE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/youtube

# ============================================================================
# INSTAGRAM LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (Advanced Access requires CNPJ)
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️ Instagram publishing (content_publish) requires Meta Advanced Access,
# which needs a CNPJ or equivalent business verification. For LOCAL
# DEVELOPMENT, use the Page Access Token bypass.
#
# How to set up for local testing ("bypass" mode):
#
# 1. Prerequisites: Facebook Page connected to Instagram Business/Creator account
# 2. Get your Instagram Business Account ID via Graph API Explorer:
#    https://developers.facebook.com/tools/explorer/
#    → Call: GET /{facebook-page-id}?fields=instagram_business_account
#    → Copy the returned instagram_business_account ID
# 3. Get a long-lived Page Access Token (same as Facebook bypass above)
# 4. Fill in the values below (uses the same Meta app as Facebook)
#
# Note: For full OAuth (when you have CNPJ), the flow is the same as
#       Facebook — add redirect URI http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/instagram
#       in Facebook Login > Settings in the Meta Developer Portal.
#
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
INSTAGRAM_APP_ID=your-facebook-app-id-here
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
INSTAGRAM_APP_SECRET=your-instagram-app-secret-here
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
INSTAGRAM_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/instagram

# ============================================================================
# INSTAGRAM WEBHOOK (Required for real-time Instagram events)
# ============================================================================
#
# Instagram uses Meta's webhook system for real-time event delivery:
#   - Comments on your posts
#   - Live video comments (live_comments)
#   - Mentions (@mentions)
#   - Story insights
#   - Direct Messages (messaging)
#
# Webhook URL to configure in Meta Developer App:
#   https://www.gabrieltoth.com/api/webhooks/instagram
#
# How to set up:
#
# 1. Go to: https://developers.facebook.com/apps/{app-id}/webhooks/
# 2. Select "Instagram" product
# 3. Set Callback URL: https://www.gabrieltoth.com/api/webhooks/instagram
# 4. Set Verify Token: any random string (this variable below)
# 5. Subscribe to fields: comments, live_comments, mentioned,
#    story_insights, messaging, messaging_optins, messaging_referrals,
#    messaging_seen
# 6. Click "Verify and Save"
#
# The App Secret above (INSTAGRAM_APP_SECRET) is used to verify
# webhook payload signatures (X-Hub-Signature-256 HMAC-SHA256).
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
INSTAGRAM_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN=your-webhook-verify-token-here

# ============================================================================
# FACEBOOK WEBHOOK (Required for real-time Facebook events)
# ===========================================================================
#
# Webhook URL: https://www.gabrieltoth.com/api/webhooks/facebook
#
# ===========================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
FACEBOOK_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN=your-webhook-verify-token-here

