# ============================================================================
# FACEBOOK LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (Advanced Access requires CNPJ)
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️ Facebook publishing requires Meta's Advanced Access for
# pages_manage_posts permission, which needs a CNPJ or equivalent business
# verification. For LOCAL DEVELOPMENT, you can bypass via a long-lived
# Page Access Token.
#
# How to get a local testing token ("bypass" mode):
#
# 1. Go to: https://developers.facebook.com/
# 2. Create or select a Facebook App
# 3. Get App ID and App Secret from App Settings > Basic
# 4. Go to: https://developers.facebook.com/tools/explorer/
# 5. Select your app, request pages_manage_posts + pages_read_engagement
# 6. Click "Get Token" → authorize
# 7. Call: GET /me/accounts → copy your Page ID and Page Access Token
# 8. Fill in the values below
#
# Note: The Page Access Token expires in ~60 days. You'll need to refresh it.
#       For PRODUCTION, you MUST have a CNPJ for Meta review.
#       For full OAuth (with CNPJ): add http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/facebook
#       in Facebook Login > Settings in the Meta Developer Portal.
#
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
FACEBOOK_APP_ID=your-facebook-app-id-here
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET=your-facebook-app-secret-here
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
FACEBOOK_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/facebook

# Facebook Page Access Token (bypass OAuth — get from Graph API Explorer)
# When set, all Facebook API calls use this token instead of OAuth flow.
# Only needed if Facebook Login OAuth is unavailable (see #oauth-bypass).
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Production/Preview
FACEBOOK_PAGE_ID=your-facebook-page-id
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Production/Preview
FACEBOOK_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Instagram Business Account Token (bypass OAuth — get from Graph API Explorer)
# When set, all Instagram API calls use this token instead of OAuth flow.
# Only needed if Instagram Login OAuth is unavailable (see #oauth-bypass).
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Production/Preview
INSTAGRAM_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID=your-instagram-business-account-id
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Production/Preview
INSTAGRAM_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=



# ============================================================================
# OAUTH STATE SECRET (Required for OAuth State Signing — YouTube, Facebook, TikTok, Instagram, Kick)
# ============================================================================
# 
# Secret key for HMAC-SHA256 signing of OAuth state tokens.
# Used by state-signer.ts to generate and verify state tokens for all OAuth flows.
# 
# How to generate a secure state secret:
# 
# 1. Use a cryptographically secure random string generator:
#    - Node.js: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#    - OpenSSL: openssl rand -hex 32
# 
# 2. Copy the generated 64-character hex string
# 3. Fill in the value below
# 
# Note: Keep this secret! Never commit it to git or share it publicly.
#       Use a different key for production.
# 
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
OAUTH_STATE_SECRET=your-64-character-hex-oauth-state-secret

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-nextauth-secret-here

# ============================================================================
# TOKEN ENCRYPTION (Required for YouTube OAuth Token Storage)
# ============================================================================
# 
# Encryption key for storing OAuth tokens securely
# 
# How to generate a secure encryption key:
# 
# 1. Use a cryptographically secure random string generator:
#    - Node.js: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#    - OpenSSL: openssl rand -hex 32
#    - Online: https://generate-secret.vercel.app/64
# 
# 2. Copy the generated 64-character hex string
# 3. Fill in the value below
# 
# Note: Keep this secret! Never commit it to git or share it publicly.
#       Use a different key for production.
# 
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-64-character-hex-encryption-key-here

# ============================================================================
# SECURE PASSWORD STORAGE (Argon2id + Pepper + CAPTCHA)
# ============================================================================
# 
# Configuration for the secure password storage system
# Implements Argon2id (memory-hard) password hashing, pepper (server-side secret),
# and CAPTCHA protection against automated attacks
# 
# ============================================================================

# Argon2id Password Hashing Parameters (Tuned for Vercel Free Plan)
# 
# Memory Cost: 64 MB (reduced from standard 128-256 MB for 10-second timeout)
# Time Cost: 3 iterations (balance between security and performance)
# Parallelism: 2 threads (fits within Free Plan CPU allocation)
# 
# Expected hash generation time: 2-3 seconds per operation
# 
# When to increase (if moving to paid plan):
# - Memory: Increase to 128MB or more
# - Time: Increase iterations (max 10)
# - Parallelism: Increase threads (max 4)
# 
# CRITICAL: These values MUST be identical in both local Docker and production Vercel!
# Changing these requires rehashing all existing passwords.
# 
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
ARGON2_MEMORY_COST=64
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
ARGON2_TIME_COST=3
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
ARGON2_PARALLELISM=2

# Pepper Secret (Server-side constant appended to passwords before hashing)
# 
# Purpose:
# - Adds security layer even if password hash database is compromised
# - Prevents offline password cracking without server access
# - Must be kept secret (never exposed, never in code)
# 
# Generation (choose one):
# - Node.js: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# - OpenSSL: openssl rand -hex 32
# - Online: https://generate-secret.vercel.app/64
# - Script: node scripts/generate-secrets.mjs
# 
# CRITICAL NOTES:
# - Must be at least 32 characters (64 hex chars)
# - Must be different from production pepper
# - For development, you can use a fixed value for testing
# - Each environment (production, staging, local dev) should have unique pepper
# 
# Development value (safe for testing):
# dev-pepper-test-very-long-string-32chars-minimum-required!
# 
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
PEPPER_SECRET=dev-pepper-test-very-long-string-32chars-minimum-required!

# CAPTCHA Configuration (Bot Protection)
# 
# Provider options:
# - "cloudflare": Cloudflare Turnstile (RECOMMENDED - zero cost)
# - "google": Google reCAPTCHA v3 (alternative - free tier + paid)
# 
# Configuration for development (Cloudflare Turnstile):
# - CAPTCHA_PROVIDER=cloudflare
# - CAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY=<test secret from Cloudflare>
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_CAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=<test site key from Cloudflare>
# 
# How to set up Cloudflare Turnstile for development:
# 1. Go to: https://dash.cloudflare.com/?to=/:account/turnstile
# 2. Create a new site or use existing
# 3. Get Site Key (public) and Secret Key (sensitive)
# 4. Fill in the values below
# 
# Test credentials (for local development):
# - CAPTCHA_PROVIDER=cloudflare
# - CAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY=1x00000000000000000000000000000000000000000
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_CAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=1x00000000000000000000000000000000000001
# 
# IMPORTANT:
# - CAPTCHA is required on registration AND login
# - Protects against brute force and account enumeration
# - Zero-cost with Cloudflare Turnstile recommended
# 
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
CAPTCHA_PROVIDER=cloudflare
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
CAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY=1x00000000000000000000000000000000000000000
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
NEXT_PUBLIC_CAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=1x00000000000000000000000000000000000001

# Rate Limiting Configuration (Brute Force Protection)
# 
# Protects against:
# - Brute force password guessing (5 failures = 15-minute lockout)
# - Credential stuffing (tries of known password dumps)
# - Account enumeration (same error for all failures)
# 
# Configuration:
# - FAILURE_THRESHOLD: Number of failures before temporary lockout
# - WINDOW_MINUTES: Time window for counting failures
# - LOCKOUT_MINUTES: Duration of temporary account lockout
# - ESCALATION_THRESHOLD: Failures before CAPTCHA difficulty increases
# 
# Values configured for development (must match docker-compose.yml):
# - RATE_LIMIT_FAILURE_THRESHOLD=5
# - RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MINUTES=15
# - RATE_LIMIT_LOCKOUT_MINUTES=15
# - RATE_LIMIT_CAPTCHA_ESCALATION_THRESHOLD=3
# 
# Typical values:
# - Strict (high security): 3 failures, 10 minute lockout
# - Standard (balanced): 5 failures, 15 minute lockout
# - Lenient (user-friendly): 10 failures, 30 minute lockout
# 
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
RATE_LIMIT_FAILURE_THRESHOLD=5
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MINUTES=15
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
RATE_LIMIT_LOCKOUT_MINUTES=15
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
RATE_LIMIT_CAPTCHA_ESCALATION_THRESHOLD=3

# ============================================================================
# TWITTER / X OAUTH (Required for Twitter/X Posting)
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: X API v2 requires the app to be enrolled in a Pay Per Use
# project. The old free tier for posting was discontinued in Feb 2026.
# Each post costs credits (~$0.015/credit, ~2 credits per post).
#
# How to get Twitter/X credentials:
#
# 1. Go to: https://console.x.com
# 2. Create a developer account (requires X login)
# 3. Select the Pay Per Use plan
# 4. Get your Organization ID from the URL: /accounts/{orgId}
# 5. Find your project ID and enrollment ID:
#    - Visit: https://console.x.com/api/accounts/{orgId}/projects
#    - Visit: https://console.x.com/api/accounts/{orgId}/structured-enrollments
# 6. Create an app via the internal API (console UI may not attach to project):
#    curl -X POST "https://console.x.com/api/client-applications" \
#      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#      -d '{"appName":"my-app","projectId":"...","enrollmentId":"...","stage":"development"}'
# 7. Assign the app to the project's Development environment:
#    curl -X POST "https://console.x.com/api/accounts/{orgId}/projects/{projectId}/client-applications/{appId}/connected" \
#      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#      -d '{"environment":"development"}'
# 8. In the app page, go to "Keys and Tokens" to generate:
#    - API Key → TWITTER_CLIENT_ID (Consumer Key)
#    - API Key Secret → TWITTER_CLIENT_SECRET (Consumer Secret)
# 9. Purchase credits at: https://console.x.com/accounts/{orgId}/billing/credits
#    - Minimum purchase ~$10
#    - ~$0.015 per text-only post (1 credit)
#    - ~$0.20 per post with links (13 credits)
#
# Note: TWITTER_CLIENT_ID is server-only (never exposed to browser)
#       TWITTER_CLIENT_SECRET is sensitive - keep it secret!
#
# Important: Users authorize via OAuth 1.0a — no static access token needed.
# The system stores user tokens encrypted in the database.
#
# ============================================================================

# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
# (Consumer Key from the X Developer Console app page)
TWITTER_CLIENT_ID=your-twitter-consumer-key-here
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ✅ SENSITIVE - Development
# (Consumer Secret from the X Developer Console app page)
TWITTER_CLIENT_SECRET=your-twitter-consumer-secret-here
# Twitter OAuth 1.0a Redirect URI (development)
# Must match what's registered in the X Developer Console > App > Callback URLs
# GitHub: ❌ DO NOT COMMIT | Vercel: ⚪ NOT SENSITIVE - Development
TWITTER_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/oauth/callback/twitter
